last_episode_to_air.name: The Greater Good
last_episode_to_air.overview: Molly and JD frantically race to the hybrids to stop a Humanich plot that will destroy the human race. Also, Lucy has a shocking realization about the GSC that forces her to question her allegiance and put Ethan at risk.

name: Extant
overview: An astronaut returns home from a year long solo mission in space. She tries to reconnect with her husband and son in their everyday life. Her experiences in space and home lead to events that ultimately will change the course of human history.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Molly Woods, an astronaut with ISEA (International Space Exploration  Agency) is assigned a 13-month solo mission aboard space station Seraphim.  She returns home to her husband John, a robotics engineer who created  their son Ethan, a prototype android called a "humanich". When Molly  discovers that she has mysteriously become pregnant despite years of  infertility, she begins a search for answers.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: After the death of her husband and losing her son Ethan, Molly Woods  battles internal and external struggles to pick the pieces of her life  back up and start fresh, this time working with the very people who  betrayed her.

episodes.name: Re-Entry
episodes.overview: Astronaut Molly Woods tries to reconnect with her husband, John, and son, Ethan, after returning from a 13-month solo mission in outer space. Molly’s mystifying experiences in space lead to events that will ultimately change the course of human history.

episodes.name: Extinct
episodes.overview: After Molly collapses and experiences a vision of her encounter on the Seraphim, Sam agrees to give her an ultrasound so she can learn more about her mysterious pregnancy. Also, Molly tracks down Kryger and he reveals the disturbing details of his own solo mission that the International Space Exploration Agency (ISEA) is keeping secret.

episodes.name: Wish You Were Here
episodes.overview: Molly has to decide if she is going to reveal her pregnancy to John after he confronts her about her distant behavior. Meanwhile, John and Molly face parents who are suspicious of Ethan when he goes to school for the first time.

episodes.name: Shelter
episodes.overview: After Sparks attempts to quarantine Molly, she and her family seek refuge on a remote island with her estranged father, Quinn. When the agency closes in on their whereabouts, Ethan is exposed to grave danger. Meanwhile, Yasumoto experiments with a strange and deadly substance.

episodes.name: What on Earth Is Wrong?
episodes.overview: John begins to doubt Molly's mental state when the validity of her pregnancy is questioned. Meanwhile, Ethan suffers a serious setback, and John and Julie disagree over how to care for him.

episodes.name: Nightmares
episodes.overview: Molly uncovers top-secret footage that reveals the real reason the ISEA chose her for the solo space mission. Meanwhile, Ethan experiences his first dream, an unforeseen event for which he was not programmed; and Julie connects with a mysterious man she meets at a gym.

episodes.name: More in Heaven and Earth
episodes.overview:
Convinced the agency has her baby, Molly is determined to find out where. Meanwhile, John discovers new and startling advancements in Ethan's programming, and Kern holds Kryger hostage in an attempt to recover the incriminating video he stole from the ISEA.

When Molly learns that her baby is alive, she sets out with Kern and Kryger to devise a plan to intercept the baby before Sparks and Yasumoto can relocate him. Meanwhile, John struggles to keep up with Ethan’s rapid development.

episodes.name: Incursion
episodes.overview: When Molly learns that her baby is alive, she sets out with Kern and Kryger to devise a plan to intercept the baby before Sparks and Yasumoto can relocate him. Meanwhile, John struggles to keep up with Ethan’s rapid development.

episodes.name: Care and Feeding
episodes.overview: When Sparks falls under the influence of the vision of his deceased daughter, he flees with Molly’s baby to a remote location. Now, Yasumoto and Molly must rely on each other to track down the offspring.

episodes.name: A Pack of Cards
episodes.overview: John makes a discovery about Yasumoto as Molly gets closer to locating her offspring; Sparks' visions of his daughter persist.

episodes.name: A New World
episodes.overview: As the offspring’s powers grow, Molly learns of Yasumoto’s painful path to immortality. When Sparks starts to have doubts about the mission, Anya takes charge. Meanwhile, Odin tries to secretly access Ethan’s circuitry.

episodes.name: Before the Blood
episodes.overview: When Molly finally comes face-to-face with her offspring, she realizes she may be the only one who can stop the coming danger. Meanwhile, Julie uncovers grave secrets about Odin.

episodes.name: Ascension
episodes.overview: Molly returns to space in an attempt redirect the Seraphim away from Earth and protect the world’s population from the deadly spores. Also, John discovers that Odin's plan has put Ethan in terrible danger.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: Molly Woods, an astronaut with ISEA (International Space Exploration  Agency) is assigned a 13-month solo mission aboard space station Seraphim.  She returns home to her husband John, a robotics engineer who created  their son Ethan, a prototype android called a "humanich". When Molly  discovers that she has mysteriously become pregnant despite years of  infertility, she begins a search for answers.

episodes.name: Change Scenario
episodes.overview: Six months after her life unraveled and dark secrets were revealed, Molly is confined to a psychiatric hospital when she learns of bizarre deaths that sound eerily similar to those she witnessed in space. When she escapes to investigate, she crosses paths with JD Richter, a determined cop who just signed on to the case.

episodes.name: Morphoses
episodes.overview: Molly and J.D. discover another pregnant woman who is suffering from inexplicable and fatal symptoms. Meanwhile, Molly begins to question her own mental stability. Julie struggles with Ethan's rebellion.

episodes.name: Empathy for the Devil
episodes.overview: Molly finally learns the frightening truth about what happened to her son. Also, Julie’s decision to erase Ethan’s memory has disturbing consequences.

episodes.name: Cracking the Code
episodes.overview: As Molly works to create a virus that will eradicate alien hybrids, she discovers that aliens are trying to communicate with humans through a hidden message in their DNA. Also, Lucy helps Ethan run away from Charlie in order to help him recover memories of his mother, Molly.

episodes.name: The New Frontier
episodes.overview: Molly discovers Ethan is alive and sets out to get her son back. Also, suspicions about John’s death cause JD to investigate Julie’s potential involvement.

episodes.name: You Say You Want an Evolution
episodes.overview: Molly panics when she discovers she is changing physically – the question is into what, and whether she can reverse what’s happening to her. Also, JD’s ex-wife, Dorothy, shows up suddenly on his doorstep to discuss their daughter.

episodes.name: The Other
episodes.overview: Molly and JD try to convince Shepherd to broker a peace between humans and hybrids. Meanwhile, Lucy tries to manipulate Charlie’s feelings to put him in a compromising position.

episodes.name: Arms and the Humanich
episodes.overview: Molly tries to save her son following a raid on the hybrid compound and JD tries to rescue his daughter from Shepherd. Elsewhere, Lucy becomes a bigger threat to humans.

episodes.name: The Other Side
episodes.overview: As Molly succumbs to the virus, long forgotten memories surface. Also, Julie is confronted with hard choices and the Hybrids seek revenge.

episodes.name: Don't Shoot the Messenger
episodes.overview: Following a near-death experience, Molly has a harrowing vision she can’t shake. Also, Shepherd's loyalty to the Global Space Commission is called into question.

episodes.name: Zugzwang
episodes.overview: Molly, JD and Ethan track down John’s mysterious former colleague who may hold the key to stopping the Humanich threat. Also, Julie enlists Charlie on a mission to find out where Lucy’s orders are coming.

episodes.name: Double Vision
episodes.overview: Molly reveals disturbing new details about Shepherd’s death to the GSC, and Lucy makes a powerful move against the humans and hybrids that could have devastating global repercussions.

episodes.name: The Greater Good
episodes.overview: Molly and JD frantically race to the hybrids to stop a Humanich plot that will destroy the human race. Also, Lucy has a shocking realization about the GSC that forces her to question her allegiance and put Ethan at risk.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: After the death of her husband and losing her son Ethan, Molly Woods  battles internal and external struggles to pick the pieces of her life  back up and start fresh, this time working with the very people who  betrayed her.
